title: SMU in, but Bama, Miami out in CFP field reveal
description: Oregon, Georgia, Boise State, Arizona State, Clemson, Texas, Penn State, Notre Dame, Ohio State, Tennessee, Indiana and SMU made the College Football Playoff.
author: Andrea Adelson

title: Tide AD to reevaluate scheduling after CFP snub
description: Alabama AD Greg Byrne said he would need to assess his nonconference scheduling philosophy moving forward after being left out of the College Football Playoff field.
author: Andrea Adelson

title: Title rivals won't slip up 'like Cucurella' - Maresca
description: Chelsea manager Enzo Maresca says Chelsea are ahead of where he expected them to be, but the Blues boss doesn't believe they are ready to be title contenders yet.

title: McLaren's 'perfect' ending after being 'on the brink'
description: McLaren's first constructors' championship since 1998 came after the team needed "great resilience and great belief" to return to the top of F1.

title: Rams overcome Josh Allen's historic 6-TD game in Week 14 classic
description: The MVP favorite added to his case with three rushing and three passing scores. That wasn't enough as Puka Nacua and Los Angeles snapped Buffalo's win streak.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: Week 14 Booms and Busts: Sam Darnold starting to look like a fantasy league winner
description: Scott Pianowski examines Week 14's fantasy winners and losers, highlighted by multiple Vikings coming through.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: 'Not a lot of quality' - Amorim warns of 'long journey' for Man Utd
description: Ruben Amorim admitted it was Manchester United's lack of quality that cost them against Nottingham Forest and again reiterated there is no quick-fix.

title: Key moment in title race? Martinelli offside 'biggest VAR decision of season'
description: Arsenal's late disallowed goal for a Gabriel Martinelli offside is the "biggest VAR decision of the season so far", says Sky Sports pundit Jamie Redknapp.
